Java Booleans
Very often, in programming, you will need a data type that can only have one of two values, lik:

- YES / NO
- ON / OFF
-TRUE / FALSE

For this, Java have a'boolean' data type, which can take the vales 'true' or 'false' .

Booleans Values
A boolean type is declared with the 'boolean' keyword and can only take the values 'true' or 'false' :

